.TH OCP 1 "January 9, 2022"
.SH NAME
ocp \- music player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocp
.RI "[ options ] [ playlist ] [ modulename ]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual page documents briefly the
.B ocp
command.
.PP
\fBocp\fP is a music player which can play music modules (ahx, mdl, it, s3m,
xm, mod), wave, audio CD, qoa, sid, midi, mp3, adlib, flac, ym, and ogg vorbis.
.PP
The player has a built\-in file selector which can be configured using alt\-c.
.PP
At any time, press F1 to open the internal help-browser or ALT+k to see a list
of the possible short-keys at your current view.
.PP
If ran with SDL output mode, some extra graphical effects are available.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.IP \-h
Show summary of options.
.IP \-c
Use specific configuration.
.IP \-f
Fileselector settings
.IP \-v
Sound settings
.IP \-s
Device settings
.IP \-p
Quit when playlist is empty.
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
\fBocp \-fl0,r1 \-vf2 \-spdevpdisk \-sr48000 fegolhuz.xm\fR
.PP
Renders the module to HD.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR oggenc (1),
.BR flac (1),
.BR lame (1).

